<TITLE> 'Mega projects' could meet regional energy needs: Dipu Moni </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 23 (bdnews24.com)Foreign minister Dipu Moni has stressed the need for 'mega power projects' in the SAARC region to solve its growing energy crisis. The minister also underscored the need to ensure due share of waters of common rivers for member counries, in talks with the visiting SAARC secretary-general Sheel Kant Sharma on Monday. Sharma, who arrived in Dhaka on Sunday, met Dipu Moni at her foreign ministry office to inform her about the projects undertaken under the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation. Neither Dipu Moni nor the secretary-general talked to waiting reporters afterwards. A foreign ministry statement said: "The minister stressed integration with a view to fighting terrorism, resolving water, energy and power crises and strengthening connectivity". On elimination of terrorism from the region the minister spoke of the South Asia task force proposed by Bangladesh, said the statement. She also suggested sub-regional initiatives such as mega-power projects to resolve the power crisis. Sheel Kant Sharma said SAARC was implementing two projects, 'Empowerment of Women' and `Maternal and Child Health', under the auspices of the SAARC Development Fund. The latter would be implemented initially in Bangladesh, Bhutan and Nepal, said the statement.
